      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 43: The generated Meson cross file does not define binaries such as c, cpp, ar, strip, pkg-config, or exe_wrapper. Meson cross builds generally require a [binaries] section; otherwise it may pick build-machine tools or fail depending on the environment. Generate the cross file from the configured toolchain variables so Harfbuzz is built for HOST, not BUILD.\n```suggestion\nprintf \"[binaries]\\nc \u003d \u0027$(CC)\u0027\\ncpp \u003d \u0027$(CXX)\u0027\\nar \u003d \u0027$(AR)\u0027\\nstrip \u003d \u0027$(STRIP)\u0027\\npkg-config \u003d \u0027$(PKG_CONFIG)\u0027\\n\\n[host_machine]\\nsystem \u003d \u0027$$SYS\u0027\\ncpu_family \u003d \u0027$$CPU_FAM\u0027\\ncpu \u003d \u0027$$CPU\u0027\\nendian \u003d \u0027little\u0027\\n\\n[properties]\\nneeds_exe_wrapper \u003d true\\n\" \u003e $@\n```",
      "revId": "1988cfe0f995f80694f069557c5397f9a68462b3",
