      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 2075: When a plugin returns no bodyOverwrite for a message that previously had one, loadMissingBodyOverwrites() leaves the stale overwrite in place because it only writes on non-empty values. This is reachable after plugin preference/language changes or plugin behavior changes: reloadBodyOverwriteMessages() clears first, but loadMissingBodyOverwrites() is also used after loads and can preserve obsolete data already cached. Explicitly erase bodyOverwrite when the transform result is missing or empty, and signal if the cached value changed.\n```suggestion\nconst auto newValue \u003d boIt !\u003d single[0].pluginData.end() ? boIt-\u003esecond : std::string{};\nstd::lock_guard writeLk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\nauto realIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(work.id);\nif (realIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n    if (newValue.empty())\n        realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n    else\n        realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d newValue;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "1988cfe0f995f80694f069557c5397f9a68462b3",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
