      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2256: SwarmLoaded is emitted before loadMissingBodyOverwrites() runs, so the initial loaded payload still contains untranslated/unmodified bodies. The new ChatHandler API comment says plugins are called before SwarmLoaded is emitted, but this implementation emits the stale messages first and then sends follow-up SwarmMessageUpdated signals, causing clients to briefly render the wrong body and making clients that only consume SwarmLoaded miss plugin data. Run the overwrite loading before emitting, and inject the transformed messages into the payload passed to SwarmLoaded, e.g. expose a synchronous helper returning the updated vector and use it before emitSignal.\n```suggestion\nconv-\u003econversation-\u003eloadMessages(\n    [accountId \u003d pimpl_-\u003eaccountId_, conversationId, id, convWeak](auto\u0026\u0026 messages) mutable {\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\n        if (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n            messages \u003d convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites(std::move(messages));\n#endif\n        emitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n    },\n    options);\n```",
      "revId": "1988cfe0f995f80694f069557c5397f9a68462b3",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
